  "prompt": "What is Fiverr, and how do they make money?",
  "response": "Fiverr is an online marketplace that connects freelancers (called \"sellers\") with clients (called \"buyers\") who need various digital services. Here's how it works:\n\n1. Business Model:\n- Sellers offer services called \"gigs\" in categories like graphic design, writing, programming, marketing, and more\n- Initially, services started at $5 (hence the name), but now prices vary widely\n- Fiverr takes a percentage of each transaction\n\n2. Revenue Model:\n- Fiverr charges sellers a 20% commission on each completed gig\n- Buyers pay a small service fee (around 5.5%) on top of the gig price\n- They also offer premium services like Fiverr Pro with higher-quality freelancers\n\n3. Additional Revenue Streams:\n- Fiverr Business (for companies seeking team collaboration)\n- Fiverr Learn (online courses for skill development)\n- Promoted gigs and advertising within the platform\n\n4. Key Features:\n- User reviews and ratings\n- Secure payment system\n- Dispute resolution\n- Communication tools\n- Multiple service categories\n\nFiverr makes money by facilitating transactions between freelancers and clients, taking a cut of each sale while providing a platform that benefits both parties.",
